<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="291" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,903,1579]" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,939,966]" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species is close to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hu, Laszlo, Ronkay &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2013" box="[656,835,940,966]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Evonima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinonanlinga">
<emphasis box="[656,835,940,966]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">E. sinonanlinga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on forewing patterns compared with other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1865" box="[1337,1437,941,966]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Evonima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1337,1437,941,966]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">Evonima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species. The main differences on the forewing patterns are follows: each line is blackish brown in the new species compared with the black line in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hu, Laszlo, Ronkay &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2013" box="[506,682,1012,1038]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Evonima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinonanlinga">
<emphasis box="[506,682,1012,1038]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">E. sinonanlinga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; in the new species the basal line is invisible, but in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hu, Laszlo, Ronkay &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2013" box="[1260,1436,1012,1038]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Evonima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinonanlinga">
<emphasis box="[1260,1436,1012,1038]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">E. sinonanlinga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the basal line is present and arc-shaped; in the new species the subterminal line is closer to the terminal line than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hu, Laszlo, Ronkay &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Evonima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinonanlinga">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">E. sinonanlinga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; in the new species the median fascia is brown, but dark orange-brown in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hu, Laszlo, Ronkay &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2013" box="[1130,1307,1084,1110]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Evonima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinonanlinga">
<emphasis box="[1130,1307,1084,1110]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">E. sinonanlinga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="291" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,903,1579]" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1119,1146]" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">Description.</emphasis>
Adult (
<figureCitation box="[429,513,1120,1146]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1804,1829]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,163,1765]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,151,1779]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–15. Evonima spp., adult, male and female genitalia. 2. E. shajiamaensis; 3. comparison of forewings (a. E. shajiamaensis; b. E. sinonanlinga; c. paratype-No. hyq429; d. paratype-No. hyq852). 4. E. xanthoplaga (after Han &amp; Hu, 2019). 5. E. lancangensis (after Han &amp; Hu, 2019). 6. E. aperta (after Han &amp; Hu, 2019). 7. E. ochritincta (after László et al., 2010). 8. E. elegans. 9. E. mandschuriana. 10. E. ronkaygabori (after Han &amp; Hu, 2019). 11 &amp; 12. E. sinonanlinga. 11. male adult; 12. female genitalia. 13–15. E. tianmuensis sp. nov. 13. male adult (holotype); 14 &amp; 15. male genitalia (holotype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3707319" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3707319/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Wingspan 
<quantity box="[652,734,1120,1147]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="291" unit="mm" value="20.0">20 mm</quantity>
. Head grayish white; antenna brown, bipectinate; labial palpus short, stretched forward, mostly covered with brown scales. Thorax grayish white with black, collar grayish white. Abdomen darker brown. Forewing ground color grayish white with pale brown, the costal line and the terminal area brown, the median fascia orange-brown; basal line invisible; antemedial line blackish brown, just present after cell; medial line invisible; postmedial line blackish brown, excurved and arc-shaped to Vein Cu 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1177,1185,1282,1296]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">2</subScript>
, then straight to inner margin; subterminal line blackish brown, wavy; terminal line blackish brown; cilia pale brown. Hindwing unicolorous, pale blackish brown, discal spot invisible.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,903,1579]" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,371,1371,1398]" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[386,540,1371,1398]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1804,1829]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,163,1765]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,151,1779]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–15. Evonima spp., adult, male and female genitalia. 2. E. shajiamaensis; 3. comparison of forewings (a. E. shajiamaensis; b. E. sinonanlinga; c. paratype-No. hyq429; d. paratype-No. hyq852). 4. E. xanthoplaga (after Han &amp; Hu, 2019). 5. E. lancangensis (after Han &amp; Hu, 2019). 6. E. aperta (after Han &amp; Hu, 2019). 7. E. ochritincta (after László et al., 2010). 8. E. elegans. 9. E. mandschuriana. 10. E. ronkaygabori (after Han &amp; Hu, 2019). 11 &amp; 12. E. sinonanlinga. 11. male adult; 12. female genitalia. 13–15. E. tianmuensis sp. nov. 13. male adult (holotype); 14 &amp; 15. male genitalia (holotype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3707319" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3707319/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">Figs 14 &amp; 15</figureCitation>
). Uncus rather long and tapering, apically pointed; tegumen narrow, elongated; valva moderately long, broadly rounded apically; costal margin slightly sclerotized; saccus small, tongue-shaped; harpe short, finely dentate. Aedeagus short; vesica without cornuti.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,903,1579]" box="[199,418,1480,1506]" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,1480,1506]" pageId="5" pageNumber="291">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
